# Userscripts Repository Rules

## Scope

Applies to all `*.user.js` files in this repository.

## Script Header Requirements

Every userscript must include:

- `@name`
- `@namespace`
- `@version`
- `@description`
- `@match` (prefer explicit URL patterns)
- `@grant` (use `none` unless API access is required)
- `@downloadURL`
- `@updateURL`
- `@run-at` (default `document-idle`)

## Code Style

- Prefer plain JavaScript without build tooling.
- Use `const` by default, `let` only when reassignment is needed.
- Keep script logic in small named functions.
- Avoid magic numbers: extract thresholds to top-level constants.
- Add brief comments only for non-obvious behavior.

## DOM Safety

- Query DOM defensively; handle missing elements gracefully.
- Avoid assumptions about exact GitHub DOM shape when possible.
- Do not throw on partial page matches.

## Performance

- Avoid tight polling loops.
- Prefer `MutationObserver` with scheduling/debouncing.
- Ensure idempotent DOM updates (no repeated duplicate badges/nodes).

## Compatibility

- Keep compatibility with modern Chromium browsers.
- Avoid experimental APIs unless absolutely needed.
